            <debateSection name="amendments" eId="sub1">
                <heading>Amendments</heading>
            </debateSection>
            <debateSection eId="sec1" name="section">
                <p>Under <ref eId="ref1" href="/ak/bill/234/main#sec5">SECTION FIVE</ref>, Government introduced an amendment which seeks to take into account all sectors of activities covered by the reevaluation of the nature of investments giving rise to exemption from taxation of capital gains tax, referring the modalities for application of this provision to the regulatory instrument.  </p>
                <p>This amendment was accepted by your Committee and <ref href="/ak/bill/234/main#sec5-subsec7" eId="ref2">SECTION FIVE (7)</ref> is reformulated as follows:
                    <mod eId="mod1">
                        <ref href="/ak/bill/234/main#sec5-subsec7" eId="ref3">SECTION FIVE:</ref>
                        “ <quotedStructure eId="qtd1">
                            <subsection eId="sec5-subsec7">
                                <content>
                                    <p>
                                        <mmod eId="mod1-mmod1">
                                            <ref href="/ak/bill/345/main#sec10" eId="ref4">Section Ten </ref> of the Finance Law of the 2010 financial year is hereby amended and supplemented as follows:
                                            
                                            <mod eId="mod1-mmod1-mod1">
                                                <quotedText eId="qtd2">1)	 A legal system for the revaluation of tangible and intangible depreciable and non-depreciable fixed assets is hereby instituted.</quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            <omissis>…………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………</omissis>
                                            <mod eId="mod1-mmod1-mod3">
                                                <quotedText eId="qtd3"> 4)	Revaluation shall be carried out no later than 31 December 2013.</quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            <omissis>…………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………………
                                                ……					</omissis>
                                            <mod eId="mod1-mmod1-mod4">
                                                <quotedText eId="qtd4">6) The revaluation surplus shall be subject to a 5% levy in discharge from 
                                                    any other tax, duty, levy and royalty.</quotedText>
                                            </mod>
                                            <mod eId="mod1-mmod1-mod5">
                                                <quotedText eId="qtd5">7) However, the above 5% levy in discharge shall not be applicable in the            case of reinvestment of the revaluation surplus within two fiscal years ended, in accordance with the forms and conditions specified in Sections 105 et seq of the General Tax Code by regulation.</quotedText>
                                            </mod>”
                                        </mmod>
                                    </p>
                                </content>
                            </subsection>
                        </quotedStructure>
                    </mod>
                </p>
                <scene>SECTION FIVE was adopted after this amendment.</scene>
